bug.short_desc: Chrome-specific issue: The Fade-Out-Effect makes the browser-scrollbars darker instead of lighter

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 878 operafadeout.zip
See attached screenshot FadeoutEffectComparison.png: We are using a fade-out-effect (qx.fx.effect.core.Fade) to fade out a GUI-element that has native scrollbars. This effect works fine in all browsers except for the Chrome 8. This fade-out-effect in Chrome makes the native scrollbars darker instead of lighter.
This issue can be reproduced with the attacht stand-alone programm operafadeout.zip.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
